main event: The crew of an aircraft sighted an amber object overtaking and passing their aircraft in Labrador on November 11, 1956.
interesting points: The object was thought to be a jet-type aircraft, The crew observed the object for 15-20 seconds, The object pulled ahead rapidly and disappeared, No radar contact or air traffic was present at the time, Subsequent information indicated the object was likely a rocket being tested by the USS Rushmore.
